.TH RFCP 1 "$Date: 2002/04/04 15:00:35 $" CASTOR "Rfio User Commands"
.SH NAME
rfcp \- Remote file copy
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rfcp
[
.BI -s " size"
] [
.BI -v2
]
.IR filename1
.IR filename2
.br
.B rfcp
[
.BI -s " size"
] [
.BI -v2
]
.IR filename
.IR directory
.br
.B rfcp
[
.BI -a
] [
.BI -b
] [
.BI -s " size"
] [
.BI -v2
]
.BI @ command_file
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX "\fLrfcp\fR"
The remote file I/O copy program provides an interface to the
.B shift
remote file I/O daemon (rfiod) for transferring files between remote and/or
local hosts. Each
.IR filename
or
.IR directory
argument is either a remote file name of the form:
.IP
.IB hostname : path
.LP
or a local file name (not containing the :/ character combination).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-a
tells
.B rfcp
that the source file is ASCII text (Windows/NT only)
.TP
.BI \-b
tells
.B rfcp
that the source is a binary file (Windows/NT only)
.TP
.BI \-s " size"
If specified, only
.I size
bytes will be copied
.TP
.BI \-v2
If specified, forces the RFIO V.2 protocol.
.SH RETURN CODES
\
.br
0	Ok.
.br
1	Bad parameter.
.br
2	System error.
.br
28	No space left on device.
.br
196	Request killed.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rcp(1), 
.BR rfiod(1)
